		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I was just reading a post from another message board about this level 18 paly asking help on what weapon to buy.&nbsp;&nbsp;His problem is "I have 1k to spend but I don't know which weapon to buy". <br>I am a level 20 paladin and I have played the game honestly(I don't know about smartly though).  That means no twinks and power leveling.  At level 20, I can't recall having more than 300pp in the bank.  I have made some plats but after all the upgrade and dressing up, i cant seem to save pp that much.  I currently have BiBs for 2hs and crystal fiber for 1hs and both cost for merely a little over 100pp.  I wouldn't mind doing quests for good weapons but if I have the resources of acquiring them safely and quickly, then it would be a no-brainer, heck yah I'm gonna buy them! <br>I've also done all the easy-money stuff, GLS quests, lego pads, cb belts...etc and I know there is a lot of twinking going on of which I don't really care for that much. Even being in unrest, all that loot and go to bank does get old after a while.<br>Now, if there is a way of getting 1k at level 18 faster and without twinking, I'd be sporting me a ghoulbane and a faster 2hs weapon.  If any of you knows of a way to get that kind of cash at that level, how and where, I would very much like to hear from you.<br>Other than that, this game rules!!!<br><br>Good Journey to you all,<br>Fellow Paly<br>20th season<br>Cazic Thule server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jan 31st 4:01 AM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9808928211447&num=3&page=&post=1&replyto=98091349715138"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=98091349715138></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=6400"><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>100 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=ZomorSoulsaver&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, some people may have twinked, some just may have gotten extremely lucky with things dropping, and some may have spent over 2 weeks getting money. If you have just been playing through the levels, you should have at LEAST 300pp with the good weapons you have. Since you are lvl 20, the BIBS is a good sword for you to use, and you DO have another good 1hs. Remember, at your lvl, you will hit for a lot more than 20 or so with the BIBS. That should be good for you till about lvl 25 or so. If you do want to make some money+ leveling at your level, i suggest going to Highpass, and making a gnoll group. There are Ringmail drops here, and rawhide armor. Also, you have a chance at a great shield + a good sword if you hunt a bit here. youll prolly want to keep the sword and the shield if you get them, the shield should last through 35 or so, your *New*, hopefully 1hs sword should last you through about lvl 25, where you can sell that for a bit, and maybe buy something else. Also, if you REALLY want to be frugal, get a guide to Lguk, and shout there for someone to tell you if shin greaves drop. Those are fairly good, no drop legs, and you MIGHT be able to get Shin Guantlets while you are there. If you pick up these, you can sell your old stuff for a few pp or some good pp. If you see someone leave stuff on a corpse of something you cant kill, loot it, there will be most likely some FS weapons or something. At your level, the only real good "easy-cash" method is GLS quest. And that just SUCKS doing it. If you work hard enough though, you might be able to get up near 1kpp in about a week of 3 hours playing periods. Thats all my advice, besides, if you work towards making levels, you will probably be able to get loot along with that. Dont give up, the road is hard but the payoff is good. Last advice-SAVE YOUR MONEY FOR LATER WHEN YOU REALLY NEED IT, BELIEVE ME!<br>Zomor-bertoxx</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
